Another good reason to use alcohol (Ethanol or 90%+ IPA) is it
doesn't tend to oxidize stuff.  If you wash it, even briefly, in
water it can get trapped inside all sorts of parts and sit for some
time, rusting things away.  It needs to be heated to drive out the
water.  And even then it's iffy.

My daughter recently dropped her cell phone in a toilet.  When I took
it apart there was corrosion all over the place.  I actually got it
back to a semi-working condition.  Unfortunately, not a useable
condition.  But I did flush it out with IPA which I'm pretty sure
helped bring it back from dead to semi-working.  If I had gotten it
right away I might have saved it.
