Couldn't you just yank off the key caps and wash them
separately?  I mean, if you're going to take the time
and trouble to clean a keyboard, why not do it
thoroughly?

You can even shortcut this a bit by putting the key
caps (*just* the key caps, thanks) into a lingerie bag
and running them through the dishwasher.  Granted,
this assumes that your particular key plastics can
withstand Very Hot Water and that may not be a given
with some of today's keyboards.

